\033[1m\033[36mfk - Context-aware AI command generator\033[0m

\033[1mDESCRIPTION:\033[0m
  Like ff, but with context awareness. Automatically includes directory listing
  and terminal history. Can also load specific files for better suggestions.

\033[1mUSAGE:\033[0m
  fk [options] <description of what you want to do>

\033[1mOPTIONS:\033[0m
  -f, --file <file>    Include file content as context (repeatable)
  --no-history         Exclude terminal history from context
  --no-dir            Exclude directory listing from context
  -h, --help          Show this help message

\033[1mEXAMPLES:\033[0m
  fk update the npm script                    # Uses dir + history context
  fk -f package.json add a test script        # Include package.json
  fk -f src/app.js -f .env fix the port      # Multiple files
  fk --no-history clean up these files        # Exclude command history
  fk --no-dir --no-history simple command     # Minimal context

\033[1mFEATURES:\033[0m
  • All features from ff command
  • Automatic directory listing context (ls -la)
  • Recent terminal history (last 10 commands)
  • File content loading with -f flag
  • Smart context-aware suggestions

\033[1mCONTEXT INCLUDED:\033[0m
  • Current directory listing (first 20 items)
  • Last 10 terminal commands
  • Any files specified with -f flag
  • Current working directory path

\033[1mCONFIGURATION:\033[0m
  Uses same OpenRouter config as ff command:
    {
      "openrouter": {
        "apiKey": "your-api-key-here",
        "model": "your-preferred-model"
      }
    }

\033[1mNOTES:\033[0m
  • File contents limited to first 100 lines each
  • Large contexts may increase response time
  • In zsh: Command appears directly in input buffer
  • In bash: Command saved to history, press ↑ to use